author: Andy Pasztor
title: NASA Budget Proposal Emphasizes Public-Private Ventures
text:
The White House is seeking to jump-start human space exploration with seed money for public-private missions orbiting the Earth and the moon, but U.S. astronauts aren’t projected to return to the lunar surface until at least the mid-2020s.
NASA’s proposed $19.9 billion budget—a roughly 3% increase from current spending—reflects President Donald Trump’s previously announced desire to enhance the use of commercial technologies and corporate partnerships aimed at eventually establishing U.S. pre-eminence “around and on the moon.”
